Software Requirements Specification for MobileMechanic
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) outlines the functional and non-functional requirements for MobileMechanic, a mobile-first platform designed for users in Pakistan to book on-demand car maintenance and repair services at their preferred locations (e.g., home or office). The document serves as a blueprint for developers, designers, and stakeholders to align on system features, technical constraints, and development priorities.
1.2 Scope
MobileMechanic enables users to:
•	Register and manage profiles with vehicle details.
•	Browse and book car maintenance services (e.g., oil change, tyre repair, battery replacement).
•	Track assigned mechanics in real-time via maps.
•	Process secure payments through local gateways (e.g., JazzCash, Easypaisa).
•	View service history and provide mechanic ratings.
•	Allow mechanics to register, manage availability, and complete jobs.
•	Provide admins with a dashboard to oversee bookings, mechanics, and analytics.
The system includes native iOS/Android apps, a backend with RESTful APIs, and integrations with maps, payment, and notification services.
1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations
•	User/Customer: Vehicle owner using the platform.
•	Mechanic: Certified professional offering maintenance services.
•	Admin: Backend operator managing users, bookings, and analytics.
•	Booking: A scheduled appointment for a car maintenance service.
•	SLA: Service Level Agreement defining response times and quality standards.
•	PSP: Payment Service Provider (e.g., JazzCash, Easypaisa).
•	OTP: One-Time Password for authentication.

