9. MVP vs. Future Enhancements
9.1 Minimum Viable Product (MVP) – Phase 1
•	User sign-up/login with OTP (FR-1, FR-3).
•	Car profile creation and service booking (FR-2, FR-4–FR-7).
•	Mechanic registration and availability toggle (FR-16, FR-17).
•	Real-time booking assignment and tracking (FR-8–FR-10).
•	Payment via JazzCash/Easypaisa and cash (FR-11–FR-13).
•	Service history and ratings (FR-14, FR-15).
•	Basic admin dashboard (bookings, revenue, mechanic list) (FR-20–FR-22).
9.2 Future Enhancements – Phase 2+
•	Subscription plans for regular maintenance (e.g., monthly oil checks).
•	Emergency roadside assistance with 24/7 support.
•	Predictive maintenance reminders based on vehicle data.
•	AI chatbot for booking assistance and FAQs.
•	Fleet management for corporate clients with multiple vehicles.
10. Technical Architecture
10.1 Tech Stack
•	Frontend: React Native for iOS/Android apps (cross-platform, reusable code).
•	Backend: Django REST Framework (Python) for APIs, authentication, and dispatch logic.
•	Database: PostgreSQL for relational data (users, bookings, payments).
•	Real-time Features: Socket.IO for mechanic tracking and notifications.
•	External Services:
o	Google Maps API for geolocation and routing.
o	JazzCash/Easypaisa for payments.
o	Firebase Cloud Messaging for push notifications.
o	Twilio for SMS/OTP.
•	Admin Panel: React.js with Tailwind CSS for responsive web dashboard.
10.2 System Architecture
•	Client Layer: Mobile apps for customers and mechanics, web app for admins.
•	API Layer: RESTful APIs for CRUD operations, authentication (JWT), and real-time updates.
•	Data Layer: PostgreSQL with tables for users, vehicles, bookings, payments, and mechanics.
•	External Services: Integrated via secure API calls (HTTPS).
11. Constraints
•	Regulatory: Compliance with Pakistan’s data protection laws (e.g., Personal Data Protection Bill).
•	Geographical: Initial rollout limited to major cities (Lahore, Karachi, Islamabad).
•	Network: App functionality depends on reliable 3G/4G or Wi-Fi access.
•	Payment: Limited to local PSPs initially, with potential delays in API integration.
